        <h3>Building ethical AI</h3>
        <p>Computer logic is only as sound as the data that feeds it. If an AI learns biased inputs, it will output biased decisions. This can even challenge organizations with the best of intentions. It’s not always apparent when a strategy contains an implicit bias, but it’s essential for AI practitioners to identify it and adjust accordingly.</p>

