       <h2>What can AI and ML do for enterprise processes?</h2> 
       <p>Numerous industries already use AI for more efficiency, accuracy, and better customer experiences. It’s also powerful for enterprise business process management, where it can analyze and consolidate workflows, automate back-end tasks, and flag redundant processes. The result? Streamlining at every step.</p>
       <h3>Benefits of AI-powered automation</h3>
       <ul>
        <li><strong>Reduce human error</strong>, especially in processes that involve analyzing numerical or textual data. AI won’t make oversights due to fatigue or error, like the way a human might.</li>
        <li><strong>Increase operational efficiency</strong>by automating more tasks and identifying and consolidating redundant processes.</li>
        <li><strong>Empower employees</strong> By automating rote tasks and allowing more time to focus on meaningful, higher-order responsibilities, AI tools can take strain off workers and allow them to maximize their talent.</li>
       </ul>

